<HL>
   Salant Posts 1st-Period Loss
</HL>
<DATE>
05/14/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C14
</SO>
<CO>
   SLT
</CO>
<IN>
EARNINGS (ERN)
</IN>
<LP>
   NEW YORK -- Salant Corp., citing a depressed retail
environment, said its first-quarter net loss widened to $2.3
million, or 67 cents a share, from $427,000, or 12 cents a
share, a year earlier.
   Sales for the apparel maker fell 7.8% to $101.9 million
from $110.5 million.
